short.am,ar,bg,bn,ca,cs,da,de,el,en,en_AU,en_G: Show indexed results for site-specific searches.

long.am,ar,bg,bn,ca,cs,da,de,el,en,en_AU,en_G: It shows the estimated amount of URLs returned when a user enters site:[url] in Google Search. In a recent update the UI in Google Search. The indexing number is not as visible to users, you have to click tools to access it. With this extension it makes it easier to do so. This extension was developed by Ryan Collins PhD from Go Fish Digital. We do not collection user information from this plugin. Reach out to https://gofishdigital.com/ with further questions.
